{"DEBACCHATE":[{"def":"To rave as a bacchanal.","pos":""}],"DEBACCHATION":[{"def":"Wild raving or debauchery.","pos":""}],"DEBACLE":[{"def":"A breaking or bursting forth; a violent rush or flood of waters which breaks down opposing barriers, and hurls forward and disperses blocks of stone and other débris.","pos":""}],"DEBAR":[{"def":"To cut off from entrance, as if by a bar or barrier; to preclude; to hinder from approach, entry, or enjoyment; to shut out or exclude; to deny or refuse; -- with from, and sometimes with of.","pos":""}],"DEBARB":[{"def":"To deprive of the beard.","pos":""}],"DEBARK":[{"def":"To go ashore from a ship or boat; to disembark; to put ashore.","pos":""}],"DEBARKATION":[{"def":"The debarkation, therefore, had to take place by small steamers.","pos":""}],"DEBARMENT":[{"def":"Hindrance from approach; exclusion.","pos":""}],"DEBARRASS":[{"def":"To disembarrass; to relieve.","pos":""}],"DEBASE":[{"def":"To reduce from a higher to a lower state or grade of worth, dignity, purity, station, etc.","pos":""}],"DEBASED":[{"def":"Turned upside down from its proper position; inverted; reversed.","pos":""}],"DEBASEMENT":[{"def":"The act of debasing or the state of being debased.","pos":""}],"DEBASER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, debases.","pos":""}],"DEBASINGLY":[{"def":"In a manner to debase.","pos":""}],"DEBATABLE":[{"def":"Liable to be debated; disputable; subject to controversy or contention; open to question or dispute; as, a debatable question.","pos":""}],"DEBATE":[{"def":"To engage in combat for; to strive for.","pos":""},{"def":"To contend for in words or arguments; to strive to maintain by reasoning; to dispute; to contest; to discuss; to argue for and against.","pos":""}],"DEBATEFUL":[{"def":"Full of contention; contentious; quarrelsome.","pos":""}],"DEBATEFULLY":[{"def":"With contention.","pos":""}],"DEBATEMENT":[{"def":"Controversy; deliberation; debate.","pos":""}],"DEBATER":[{"def":"One who debates; one given to argument; a disputant; a controvertist.","pos":""}],"DEBATING":[{"def":"The act of discussing or arguing; discussion.","pos":""}],"DEBATINGLY":[{"def":"In the manner of a debate.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCH":[{"def":"To lead away from purity or excellence; to corrupt in character or principles; to mar; to vitiate; to pollute; to seduce; as, to debauch one's self by intemperance; to debauch a woman; to debauch an army.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHED":[{"def":"Dissolute; dissipated.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHEDLY":[{"def":"In a profligate manner.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHEDNESS":[{"def":"The state of being debauched; intemperance.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHEE":[{"def":"One who is given to intemperance or bacchanalian excesses; a man habitually lewd; a libertine.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHER":[{"def":"One who debauches or corrupts others; especially, a seducer to lewdness.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHERY":[{"def":"Corruption of fidelity; seduction from virtue, duty, or allegiance.","pos":""},{"def":"Excessive indulgence of the appetites; especially, excessive indulgence of lust; intemperance; sensuality; habitual lewdness.","pos":""}],"DEBAUCHMENT":[{"def":"The act of corrupting; the act of seducing from virtue or duty.","pos":""}],"DEBEIGE":[{"def":"A kind of woolen or mixed dress goods.","pos":""}],"DEBELLATE":[{"def":"To subdue; to conquer in war.","pos":""}],"DEBELLATION":[{"def":"The act of conquering or subduing.","pos":""}],"DEBENTURE":[{"def":"A writing acknowledging a debt; a writing or certificate signed by a public officer, as evidence of a debt due to some person; the sum thus due.","pos":""},{"def":"A customhouse certificate entitling an exporter of imported goods to a drawback of duties paid on their importation.","pos":""}],"DEBENTURE STOCK":[{"def":"The debt or series of debts, collectively, represented by a series of debentures; a debt secured by a trust deed of property for the benefit of the holders of shares in the debt or of a series of debentures.","pos":""}],"DEBENTURED":[{"def":"Entitled to drawback or debenture; as, debentured goods.","pos":""}],"DEBILITANT":[{"def":"Diminishing the energy of organs; reducing excitement; as, a debilitant drug.","pos":""}],"DEBILITATE":[{"def":"To impair the strength of; to weaken; to enfeeble; as, to debilitate the body by intemperance.","pos":""}],"DEBILITATION":[{"def":"The act or process of debilitating, or the condition of one who is debilitated; weakness.","pos":""}],"DEBILITY":[{"def":"The state of being weak; weakness; feebleness; languor.","pos":""}],"DEBIT":[{"def":"A debt; an entry on the debtor (Dr.","pos":""}],"DEBITUMINIZATION":[{"def":"The act of depriving of bitumen.","pos":""}],"DEBITUMINIZE":[{"def":"To deprive of bitumen.","pos":""}],"DEBLAI":[{"def":"The cavity from which the earth for parapets, etc.","pos":""}],"DEBONAIR":[{"def":"Characterized by courteousness, affability, or gentleness; of good appearance and manners; graceful; complaisant.","pos":""}],"DEBONAIRLY":[{"def":"Courteously; elegantly.","pos":""}],"DEBONAIRNESS":[{"def":"The quality of being debonair; good humor; gentleness; courtesy.","pos":""}],"DEBOUCH":[{"def":"To march out from a wood, defile, or other confined spot, into open ground; to issue.","pos":""}],"DEBOUCHE":[{"def":"A place for exit; an outlet; hence, a market for goods.","pos":""}],"DEBOUCHURE":[{"def":"The outward opening of a river, of a valley, or of a strait.","pos":""}],"DEBRIS":[{"def":"Broken and detached fragments, taken collectively; especially, fragments detached from a rock or mountain, and piled up at the base.","pos":""}],"DEBRUISED":[{"def":"Surmounted by an ordinary; as, a lion is debruised when a bend or other ordinary is placed over it, as in the cut.","pos":""}],"DEBT":[{"def":"An action at law to recover a certain specified sum of money alleged to be due.","pos":""}],"DEBTED":[{"def":"Indebted; obliged to.","pos":""}],"DEBTEE":[{"def":"One to whom a debt is due; creditor; -- correlative to debtor.","pos":""}],"DEBTOR":[{"def":"One who owes a debt; one who is indebted; -- correlative to creditor.","pos":""}],"DEBULLITION":[{"def":"A bubbling or boiling over.","pos":""}],"DEBUSCOPE":[{"def":"A modification of the kaleidoscope; -- used to reflect images so as to form beautiful designs.","pos":""}],"DEBUT":[{"def":"A beginning or first attempt; hence, a first appearance before the public, as of an actor or public speaker.","pos":""},{"def":"A person who makes his (or her) first appearance before the public.","pos":""}]}